From: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] x86/mm: Force TLB flush on any PMD flag change

For deterministic execution under hypervisors with VPID enabled,
force TLB flush whenever huge PMD flags change, not just when
permissions are demoted. This is the transparent hugepage equivalent
of the PTE fix in patch 1 and prevents spurious faults from stale
TLB entries on THP mappings.

Signed-off-by: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
index abcdef123..1234567ab 100644
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/tlbflush.h
@@ -440,6 +440,13 @@ static inline bool pte_needs_flush(pte_t oldpte, pte_t newpte)
  */
 static inline bool huge_pmd_needs_flush(pmd_t oldpmd, pmd_t newpmd)
 {
+	/*
+	 * Force TLB flush on any flag change for deterministic execution
+	 * under hypervisors with VPID. Avoids spurious faults on THP.
+	 */
+	if (pmd_flags(oldpmd) != pmd_flags(newpmd))
+		return true;
+
 	/* !PRESENT -> * ; no need for flush */
 	if (!(pmd_flags(oldpmd) & _PAGE_PRESENT))
 		return false;
--
